						"description": "\nThis endpoint allows you to create a new investor using a POST request to the specified URL. The request should include the investor's username, name, risk profile, and the source of funds.\n\n### Request Body\n- `username` (string): The username of the investor.\n- `name` (string): The name of the investor.\n- `riskProfile` (string): The risk profile of the investor.\n- `sourceOfFund` (string): The source of funds for the investor.\n\n### Response\nThe response to the request will have a status code of 400, indicating a bad request. The response body will include the following fields:\n- `statusCode` (number): The status code of the response.\n- `result` (boolean): The result of the request.\n- `data` (null): This field will be null in case of an error.\n- `errors.username` (array): An array containing any errors related to the username field.\n- `pagination` (null): This field will be null in case of an error.\n\n"
